\f0\b\fs42\fsmilli21333 \cf2 Participants
\f1\b0\fs25\fsmilli12800 \
\pard\pardeftab720\fi945\sl640\sa0\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs32 \cf2 Twenty-six healthy participants (10 female) with normal or corrected-to-normal vision were recruited from the general population by means of announcements: age: mean = 37.3, sd = 9.1; education level: mean = 5.9
\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 [1]
\f0\fs32 ; verbal IQ: mean = 24.2, sd = 5.0
\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 [2]
\f0\fs32 .\'a0 The inclusion criteria were age between 18 and 60 years, and fluency in Spanish.\'a0 The exclusion criteria were neurological or mental illness, intellectual disability, head injury, alcohol or drug abuse in the past six months, and current severe physical disease, as
\f1\fs25\fsmilli12800 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl640\sa0\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs32 \cf2 well as the standard exclusion criteria for participation in fMRI procedures, namely claustrophobia and metallic implants including fitted pacemaker and cochlear implants.\'a0 This study was approved by the Parc Sanitari Sant Joan de D\'e9u ethics committee and all participants provided written informed consent before taking part in the study. 
\f1\fs25\fsmilli12800 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl640\sa0\partightenfactor0

